7. The system of claim 1, where the one of the plurality of optical transport systems further includes: a demultiplexer to: receive the respective light, demultiplex the respective light to recover the light at the plurality of different, fixed wavelengths, and output the recovered light;
a plurality of transmitters including the transmitter, each of the plurality of transmitters to: receive the recovered light at one of the plurality of different, fixed wavelengths, modulate the particular data signal on the recovered light to form the particular optical signal, and output the particular optical signal; and
another multiplexer to: receive the particular optical signals from the plurality of transmitters, multiplex the particular optical signals to form multiplexed optical signals, and output the multiplexed optical signals on the particular optical fiber.

14. A system comprising:
a first laser bank that includes a first-plurality of lasers;
a second laser bank that includes a second-plurality of lasers;
a single first multiplexer connected to the first laser bank and not connected to the second laser bank;
a single second multiplexer connected to the second laser bank and not connected to the first laser bank;
a first amplifier connected to the first multiplexer;
a second amplifier connected to the second multiplexer;
a combiner connected to the first amplifier and the second amplifier;
a first splitter connected to the combiner; and
a plurality of optical transport systems connected to the first splitter,
one of the plurality of optical transport systems including a second splitter.

20. A system comprising:
a first laser bank that includes a first-plurality of lasers;
a second laser bank that includes a second-plurality of lasers;
a single first multiplexer connected to the first laser bank and not connected to the second laser bank;
a single second multiplexer connected to the second laser bank and not connected to the first laser bank;
a first amplifier connected to the first multiplexer;
a second amplifier connected to the second multiplexer;
a first splitter connected to the first amplifier;
a second splitter connected to the second amplifier; and
a plurality of optical transport systems connected to the first splitter and the second splitter,
one of the plurality of optical transport systems including:
a combiner connected to the first splitter and the second splitter,
a demultiplexer connected to the combiner,
a plurality of transmitters connected to the demultiplexer, and
a plurality of third splitters,
each of the plurality of third splitters being connected to a respective one of the plurality of transmitters.

29. The one or more systems of claim 25, where the multiplexer corresponds to a first multiplexer, where the one of the plurality of optical transport systems includes: a demultiplexer to: receive the respective multiplexed light, demultiplex the respective multiplexed light to recover the light at the plurality of different, fixed wavelengths, and output the recovered light;
a plurality of transmitters, each of the plurality of transmitters to: receive the recovered light at one of the plurality of different, fixed wavelengths, modulate a particular data signal on the recovered light to form a particular optical signal, and output the particular optical signal; and
a second multiplexer to: receive the particular optical signals from the plurality of transmitters, multiplex the particular optical signals to form multiplexed optical signals, and output the multiplexed optical signals on a particular optical fiber of the one or more optical fibers.
